FBIS4-38053 "drnes124_l_94004" FBIS-NES-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 ISRAEL Jerusalem Council Plans To Prevent 'Arafat Visit Jerusalem Council Plans To Prevent 'Arafat Visit TA2706151294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 27 Jun 94 TA2706151294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] The Jerusalem City Council decided on a series of measures to prevent Yasir 'Arafat's visit in the city. In a special session held this morning, the mayor and all his eight deputies decided to set up three action committees: a public relations committee, a financial committee, and a committee which would organize a huge protest campaign. Our correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that, among other things, the Jerusalem City Council plans to fly in protesters from overseas aboard special planes.
